The Cartographer has a standing commission for a complete route survey of the Forest of Confusion. The forest's disorienting layout has defeated previous documentation attempts, and the Cartographer's office has never been able to issue a complete reference chart of its interior. Traverse every accessible path and clearing within the forest and return with a full navigation record.
Your Forest of Confusion survey has been accepted and filed in the Cartographer's geographic archive. The completed route record represents the first reliable documentation of the forest's full interior extent, and the Cartographer has noted this as a significant addition to the regional reference collection.

